      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p>The Christian collection of the apocryphal Acts of the Apostles is the main
            Ethiopian collection of apostolic Apocrypha. It includes single texts, mainly
            Preaching, Martyrdom, and Acts of the Apostles, translated from Arabic. The terminus ante quem for the collection is provided by  <ref type="mss" corresp="BNFet52">BNFet52</ref>, datable to <date>1379</date>. However,
            the title G.Ḥ. already appears in an inventory of books found in the
            well-known <date notBefore="1200" notAfter="1300">thirteenth-century</date> Four Gospels manuscript (<ref type="mss" corresp="EMML1832">EMML 1832</ref>) of
            Ḥayq ʾƎsṭifānos (the so-called Four Gospels book of ʾIyasus Moʾa). Six recensions are known according to <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Bausi2000Osservazioni"/>
            </bibl>, depending on the Vorlage and the selection and order of texts, see <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5811GHI"/>, <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5814GHII"/>, <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5815GHIII"/>,
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5816GHIV"/>, <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5817GHV"/> and <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5818GHVI"/>.</p>
         </abstract>
